## Authentication

**Base URL** `https://test-writechoice.onrender.com`

<Warning>
  All requests require a Bearer token in the header.

  Example: Bearer tf-live-4a8f2c1e9b3d7e6a
</Warning>

## Endpoints

Check all available API endpoints:

<Card title="POST /projects — Create project">
  You must create a project before creating any tasks.

  The `project_id` returned in the response is required to create tasks.

  **Request body**

  ```json
  {
    "name": "API Documentation Revamp",
    "description": "Rewriting all public-facing API docs."
  }
  ```

  **Example request**

  ```bash
  POST /projects
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Bearer {api_key}
  
  {
    "name": "API Documentation Revamp",
    "description": "Rewriting all public-facing API docs."
  }
  ```

  **Responses**

  `201` Project created. Returns the Project object.

  `400` Missing or invalid name field.

  `401` Missing or invalid API key.
</Card>

<Card title="POST /tasks — Create task">
  Creates a new task inside an existing project.

  Requires a valid `project_id`. Tasks are created with a default status of `pending`.

  **Request body**

  ```json
  {
    "project_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "title": "Write introduction page",
    "description": "Draft the overview and getting started sections."
  }
  ```

  **Example request**

  ```bash
  POST /tasks
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Bearer {api_key}
  
  {
    "project_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "title": "Write introduction page",
    "description": "Draft the overview and getting started sections."
  }
  ```

  **Responses**

  `201` Task created. Returns the Task object.

  `400` Missing required fields.

  `401` Missing or invalid API key.

  `404` Project not found.
</Card>

<Card title="GET /projects/{project_id}/tasks — List tasks">
  Returns all tasks belonging to a specific project. Returns an empty `tasks` array if the project exists but has no tasks yet.

  **Path parameter**

  `project_id` — The ID of the project.

  **Example request**

  ```bash
  GET /projects/a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890/tasks
  Authorization: Bearer {api_key}
  ```

  **Responses**

  `200` Returns a TaskList object with total and tasks array.

  `401` Missing or invalid API key.

  `404` Project not found.
</Card>

<Card title="PATCH /tasks/{task_id} — Update task">
  Updates one or more fields of an existing task. At least one field must be provided. Valid `status` values: `pending`, `in_progress`, `done`.

  **Path parameters**

  `task_id` — The ID of the task.

  **Request body**

  ```json
  {
    "status": "in_progress"
  }
  ```

  **Example request**

  ```bash
  PATCH /tasks/f9e8d7c6-b5a4-3210-fedc-ba9876543210
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Bearer {api_key}
  
  {
    "status": "in_progress"
  }
  ```

  **Responses**

  `200` Task updated. Returns the updated Task object.

  `400` Invalid status value or empty body.

  `401` Missing or invalid API key.

  `404` Task not found.
</Card>

<Card title="DELETE /tasks/{task_id} — Delete task">
  Deletes a task permanently. This action cannot be undone.

  **Path parameters**

  `task_id` — The ID of the task.

  **Example request**

  ```bash
  DELETE /tasks/f9e8d7c6-b5a4-3210-fedc-ba9876543210
  Authorization: Bearer {api_key}
  ```

  **Responses**

  `200` Task deleted. Returns a confirmation message.

  `401` Missing or invalid API key.

  `404` Task not found.
</Card>

## Schemas

### Project

| Field | Type |
| --- | --- |
| `project_id` | uuid |
| `name` | string |
| `description` | string \| null |
| `created_at` | date-time |

### Task

| Field | Type |
| --- | --- |
| `task_id` | uuid |
| `project_id` | uuid |
| `title` | string |
| `description` | string \| null |
| `status` | enum |
| `created_at` | date-time |
| `updated_at` | date-time |

**Status values:** `pending` `in_progress` `done`
